# Required: your OpenRouter API key (https://openrouter.ai/keys)
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-...

# Optional model overrides (CLI flags take precedence over these).
# REELMAESTRO_TEXT_MODEL=anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6
# REELMAESTRO_IMAGE_MODEL=google/gemini-3-pro-image
# REELMAESTRO_TTS_MODEL=google/gemini-3.1-flash-tts-preview
# REELMAESTRO_MUSIC_MODEL=google/lyria-3-pro-preview
# REELMAESTRO_VIDEO_MODEL=google/veo-3.1-lite
# REELMAESTRO_VOICE=Kore

# Image model options (set REELMAESTRO_IMAGE_MODEL above or --image-model; swaps EVERY image gen:
# character references, scene stills, and the poster). The model MUST accept image input, since the
# pipeline conditions each scene on reference images — all the options below do.
# Discover current ones: curl -s "https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/models" | grep -i image
#
# "x" is the rough per-reel cost relative to the default (gemini-3-pro-image).
#   Model                              vs default   Notes
#   google/gemini-3-pro-image          1x (default) best coherence + cross-scene consistency
#   google/gemini-3.1-flash-image      ~0.5x        Nano Banana 2 — half the cost, faster, weaker coherence
#   google/gemini-2.5-flash-image      ~0.3x        Older flash — a downgrade, skip
#   openai/gpt-5-image-mini            ~1.2x        OpenAI; strong instruction-following
#   openai/gpt-5.4-image-2             ~4x          Newest OpenAI; best prompt adherence + structure
#   openai/gpt-5-image                 ~5x          OpenAI flagship image, max quality
# Going up a tier also lowers --validate-scene re-rolls (fewer defects to re-roll), so the effective
# cost gap is smaller than it looks. To save money, set the flash model above. OpenAI models are a
# different family — smoke-test one scene first, since the multi-reference payload may behave
# differently than the Gemini path.

# Voice: if REELMAESTRO_VOICE/--voice is unset, it's auto-picked from the script's narrator
# gender (male -> Puck, female/neutral -> Kore). Set it here to force one voice for every run.
# Voice depends on REELMAESTRO_TTS_MODEL — each model has its own set (use --voice for one-offs).
# Discover current voices: curl -s "https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/models?output_modalities=speech"
#
# google/gemini-3.1-flash-tts-preview (default) — 30 voices. Hints: Kore=warm/curious (default),
# Charon=deep/serious, Puck=bright/conversational, Aoede=friendly, Schedar=neutral, Fenrir=energetic:
#   Zephyr Puck Charon Kore Fenrir Leda Orus Aoede Callirrhoe Autonoe
#   Enceladus Iapetus Umbriel Algieba Despina Erinome Algenib Rasalgethi Laomedeia Achernar
#   Alnilam Schedar Gacrux Pulcherrima Achird Zubenelgenubi Vindemiatrix Sadachbia Sadaltager Sulafat
#
# x-ai/grok-voice-tts-1.0: eve ara rex sal leo
#
# mistralai/voxtral-mini-tts-2603 (emotion-tagged): en_paul_{neutral,happy,sad,excited,confident,
#   cheerful,frustrated,angry}, gb_oliver_{neutral,excited,curious,confident,...}, gb_jane_{neutral,
#   sad,curious,sarcasm,...}, fr_marie_{neutral,happy,excited,curious,sad,angry}
#
# microsoft/mai-voice-2 (multilingual): en-US-Harper:MAI-Voice-2 es-MX-Valeria:MAI-Voice-2
#   fr-FR-Soleil:MAI-Voice-2 de-DE-Klaus:MAI-Voice-2

# Local word-level caption timing (whisper-timestamped). Not an OpenRouter call.
# REELMAESTRO_WHISPER_CMD=whisper_timestamped
# REELMAESTRO_WHISPER_MODEL=base

# Output toggles (also available as CLI flags --no-captions / --no-narration / --scene-seconds).
# REELMAESTRO_NO_CAPTIONS=1    # don't burn captions into the video
# REELMAESTRO_NO_NARRATION=1   # no spoken voiceover (silent or music-only video)
# REELMAESTRO_SCENE_SECONDS=4  # per-scene length used when narration is disabled
